		public threadForShadowFrames: rawFrames exception: ex ^<ThreadMirror> = (
			^threadForShadowFrames: rawFrames exception: ex doItSource: nil receiver: nil scope: nil
		)
		public threadForShadowFrames: rawFrames exception: ex doItSource: expression <String | nil> receiver: rcvr scope: rawScope <Map | nil> ^<ThreadMirror> = (
			(* Stage 3 transplant: the raw shadow-frame records built during a reconstruction unwind (innermost first: {mixin, selector, receiver, args}) become a BROKEN simulated thread the Debugging UI presents like any other. Frames are restart-quality (receiver and arguments captured at unwind, locals cleared, bci 1): inspect everything, evaluate in frame scope, restart any frame to re-execute it. Unresolvable frames (edited away, record-less) are skipped. Degrades to a frameless broken thread without the simulator.

		With a doItSource (the evaluate:with: reconstruction boundary): the doIt itself is compiled fresh with the V5 pipeline - exactly as evaluateSuspended: does - and appended as the OUTERMOST frame. The doIt is installed nowhere, so shadow-record resolution can never find it; without this the evaluation's own frame, usually the one the user cares about, is missing, and Continue has nothing meaningful to restart. *)

			| sim count frameRec simMethod act innermost prev simThread doItFrame prevSelector calleeSel siteRaw site b blkRaw blk doItMethod doItRecordFramed isDoIt recSelector |
